02:17.340 --> 02:20.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:20.470 --> 02:23.539
[TEA KETTLE WHISTLING]

02:23.540 --> 02:26.230
[WHISTLING STOPS]

02:28.732 --> 02:30.450
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

02:34.060 --> 02:36.320
[CUP CLATTERS]

02:44.860 --> 02:47.400
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

02:48.560 --> 02:51.380
[SPOON CLINKS]

02:55.580 --> 02:58.819
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

02:58.820 --> 03:00.763
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

03:00.764 --> 03:04.009
Oh, my God.

03:04.010 --> 03:05.959
Peter.

03:05.960 --> 03:08.063
I'm so sorry, I didn't
know where else to go.

03:08.064 --> 03:10.232
Get in here.

03:11.520 --> 03:13.979
I... I've gotten myself
into a situation.

03:13.980 --> 03:17.039
Everybody's looking for
you, including the police!

03:17.040 --> 03:18.782
I didn't know who else I could go to.

03:18.783 --> 03:21.739
I just came to get some advice.

03:21.740 --> 03:23.787
You've got the Rothstein
books, don't you?

03:24.980 --> 03:26.579
I don't want to tell you too much.

03:26.580 --> 03:27.699
I mean, it will put you in danger.

03:27.700 --> 03:28.916
Really?

03:28.917 --> 03:30.669
Sit down, Peter.

03:35.860 --> 03:39.845
Now, tell me what is going on.

03:41.260 --> 03:43.974
Obviously, you have the manuscripts.

03:45.240 --> 03:47.379
[SIGHS]

03:47.380 --> 03:51.059
I may have... some materials.

03:51.060 --> 03:54.234
Which you simply found in
the crashed car, right?

03:55.720 --> 03:58.399
And I went to the bookstore
owner, Halliday...

03:58.400 --> 03:59.410
Yeah?

04:00.360 --> 04:03.159
[SIGHS] He bought a poem...

04:03.160 --> 04:05.829
and now he's dead...

04:05.830 --> 04:07.869
and I don't know what to do.

04:07.870 --> 04:09.819
You're right to be scared.

04:09.820 --> 04:12.339
Halliday's dead because there's
somebody else out there

04:12.340 --> 04:13.959
looking for those books.

04:13.960 --> 04:15.219
I met him.

04:15.220 --> 04:17.005
- What do you mean, "you met him"?
- Some guy...

04:17.005 --> 04:19.059
I don't know his name, but
he knew I had the stuff.

04:19.060 --> 04:22.379
I think he's the guy who broke
into Rothstein's house.

04:22.380 --> 04:24.972
- I may have shot him.
- Jesus Christ!

04:24.973 --> 04:27.129
- How did you even get a gun?
- It's not hard.

04:27.130 --> 04:29.351
All right, we're... we're
calling the police right now.

04:29.352 --> 04:30.419
No, no, they'll put me in jail.

04:30.420 --> 04:32.104
Which may be the safest
place for you to be until...

04:32.105 --> 04:34.259
- I don't trust the police.
- Oh, Peter...

04:34.260 --> 04:35.619
No, no going to the police!

04:35.620 --> 04:37.568
This... this will destroy my parents!

04:37.569 --> 04:38.719
My dad's been through enough already.

04:38.720 --> 04:39.905
This would kill him.

04:39.906 --> 04:42.799
So, Peter... [STAMMERS]

04:42.800 --> 04:45.319
What is it that you're
looking for from me?

04:45.320 --> 04:49.699
Do you know how very
dangerous this all is?

04:49.700 --> 04:51.219
Of course I do, that's why I came.

04:51.220 --> 04:53.499
- I don't know what to do...
- No, listen to me.

04:53.500 --> 04:55.919
Bill Hodges lives right next door.

04:55.920 --> 04:57.462
No, no, he's working with the cops.

04:57.463 --> 04:59.659
- No, we can trust him.
- No, he'll turn me in.

04:59.660 --> 05:01.139
I'm... I'm sorry, this...
I shouldn't have come.

05:01.140 --> 05:02.199
What about a lawyer?

05:02.200 --> 05:04.459
A lawyer has to keep things privileged.

05:04.460 --> 05:07.540
In fact, he... he would be barred
by law from turning you in,

05:07.550 --> 05:11.019
and... and he could also
lay out your legal options

05:11.020 --> 05:13.299
much better than I.

05:13.300 --> 05:15.769
- Peter, for God's sake...
- Okay,

05:15.770 --> 05:17.439
- I'll meet with a lawyer.
- Good.

05:17.440 --> 05:20.339
But no telling Hodges
or the police anything.

05:20.340 --> 05:21.947
I'll call you.

05:26.760 --> 05:28.409
You should have called me.

05:28.410 --> 05:30.999
I had to make a fast decision,
and what am I gonna do?

05:31.000 --> 05:32.660
I... I can't restrain him.

05:32.666 --> 05:35.168
- Well, where is he now?
- I have absolutely no idea.

05:35.169 --> 05:38.359
He took off. He said he'd call me.

05:38.360 --> 05:40.859
Now... now this Finkelstein,
is he really good?

05:40.860 --> 05:42.209
Jesus balls.

05:42.210 --> 05:44.659
Yes, he's good.

05:44.660 --> 05:46.339
You could set up the appointment

05:46.340 --> 05:49.619
- and we just grab him.
- No, no, we can't do it like that.

05:49.620 --> 05:51.840
- It's for his own safety.
- Not necessarily.

05:53.100 --> 05:54.769
[SIGHS]

05:54.770 --> 05:56.982
He's armed, actually.

05:58.420 --> 06:00.259
Somebody came after him.

06:00.260 --> 06:01.419
It may have been the same person

06:01.420 --> 06:05.399
who killed Rothstein,
and Peter shot him.

06:05.400 --> 06:06.539
He what?

06:06.540 --> 06:08.359
Oh, I just can't believe I'm
betraying his confidence.

06:08.360 --> 06:09.799
Oh, for fuck's sake, Ida, come on.

06:09.800 --> 06:12.831
We have a very volatile and
dangerous situation here!

06:12.832 --> 06:14.659
He shot somebody?

06:14.660 --> 06:16.819
In the leg. And whoever
it is, is still out there,

06:16.820 --> 06:18.819
only he figures to be more angry,

06:18.820 --> 06:21.499
so I just want to broker
this meeting with the lawyer

06:21.500 --> 06:24.551
in the hopes that he can
make Peter see reason.

06:26.060 --> 06:28.555
- You don't know where he is?
- No, I don't.

06:28.556 --> 06:31.934
- Ida...
- No, no! Truly, Bill, I don't.

06:38.273 --> 06:40.149
[SIGHS]

06:40.150 --> 06:42.180
[SCOFFS]

06:44.460 --> 06:46.519
This isn't fucking good.

06:46.520 --> 06:49.079
No, it isn't.

06:49.080 --> 06:52.569
Peter's just a boy.

06:52.570 --> 06:54.719
[SIGHS]

06:54.720 --> 06:56.541
I'll get you Finkelstein's number.

06:56.542 --> 06:59.280
Yes, thank you.

07:03.440 --> 07:04.899
You okay?

07:04.900 --> 07:07.619
Yeah, yeah, I just feel... [SIGHS]

07:07.620 --> 07:09.459
surreal, I guess.

07:09.460 --> 07:11.239
I hadn't let myself hope for it...

07:11.240 --> 07:12.839
- Yeah.
- And now...

07:12.840 --> 07:14.979
Technically, you're not free.

07:14.980 --> 07:16.895
You're still under court supervision.

07:16.896 --> 07:19.159
Yeah, you already said that.

07:19.160 --> 07:21.019
But I just want to
make sure it sinks in,

07:21.020 --> 07:23.939
because if you so much violate
one condition of your release,

07:23.940 --> 07:27.039
they'll re-arrest you. You'll have
to serve the whole term in prison.

07:27.040 --> 07:30.679
- Okay.
- No missing any meetings

07:30.680 --> 07:32.759
with the parole officer or the shrink.

07:32.760 --> 07:34.899
You... you can't skip
any of the drug tests

07:34.900 --> 07:36.419
or court-ordered anger
management sessions.

07:36.420 --> 07:38.319
Yeah, okay, Roland. I'm not
gonna risk going back to jail.

07:38.320 --> 07:39.579
- You don't have to worry.
- All right, well,

07:39.580 --> 07:41.079
let's talk about your
living arrangements,

07:41.080 --> 07:42.939
and I'm assuming you
haven't got any, right?

07:42.940 --> 07:47.899
No, they repossessed my
trailer when I was in jail.

07:47.900 --> 07:49.619
You could live with me.

07:49.620 --> 07:53.040
I mean, until you find
somewhere to live.

07:54.300 --> 07:55.639
I couldn't do that.

07:55.640 --> 07:57.379
I mean, why not? You've
gotta live somewhere,

07:57.380 --> 07:58.639
and I have room.

07:58.640 --> 08:00.435
I... I'm not sure that's
the best of ideas.

08:00.436 --> 08:02.139
Yeah, but it can't be
the worst of ideas.

08:02.140 --> 08:05.459
I mean, this is going
to be a sensory shock.

08:05.460 --> 08:08.269
You know, you can talk to me.

08:08.270 --> 08:12.199
- You know that.
- Okay, I'll be the logic police.

08:12.200 --> 08:14.340
Though I'm glad that you escaped

08:14.350 --> 08:15.659
being institutionalized,

08:15.660 --> 08:19.119
I do think some voluntary
treatment is indicated.

08:19.120 --> 08:20.649
In-patient.

08:20.650 --> 08:22.899
[SIGHS]

08:22.900 --> 08:25.140
- Shit.
- Is he still talking to you?

08:27.380 --> 08:29.379
Is he?

08:29.380 --> 08:33.129
You say that like it's
totally a bad thing.

08:33.130 --> 08:34.578
[SCOFFS]

08:34.580 --> 08:36.009
Look, it was...

08:36.010 --> 08:38.299
Brady's the one that told me to get up

08:38.299 --> 08:39.759
and speak for him at the sentencing.

08:39.760 --> 08:41.818
The judge was really feeling that.

08:41.820 --> 08:43.679
That was good advice, and he advised me

08:43.679 --> 08:45.317
to call you as a witness.

08:45.318 --> 08:47.799
I mean, and you were amazing.

08:47.800 --> 08:51.039
It could be said that Brady
helped secure my freedom

08:51.040 --> 08:52.154
just as much as you did.

08:52.155 --> 08:54.559
- That's not fair.
- It shouldn't be said.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.359
Look, I am extremely grateful

08:56.360 --> 08:59.779
for everything that you've
done for me, and...

08:59.780 --> 09:01.540
I know that you fought for me...

09:02.918 --> 09:04.919
but so has Brady, that's all I'm saying.

09:04.920 --> 09:06.179
And all I'm saying is,

09:06.180 --> 09:08.299
is that if Brady is still in your head

09:08.300 --> 09:12.279
and he's giving you advice
and you're taking it...

09:12.280 --> 09:13.799
we have a problem.

09:13.800 --> 09:15.499
Look, there's advantages and drawbacks

09:15.500 --> 09:16.979
to Brady being in my head.

09:16.980 --> 09:18.683
The key is to know which one is which.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.180
I know.

09:24.106 --> 09:27.689
[CAR DOOR OPENS, SLAMS]

09:27.690 --> 09:29.819
He's gone into hiding?

09:29.820 --> 09:31.759
That's the word.

09:31.760 --> 09:33.039
He hasn't come home.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.158
Parents have contacted the police.

09:35.159 --> 09:36.699
Shit,

09:36.700 --> 09:38.495
- this will make things more difficult.
- [SCOFFS]

09:38.496 --> 09:40.579
Yeah, tell me about it.

09:40.580 --> 09:43.249
Do the police suspect that
he's got the manuscripts?

09:43.250 --> 09:45.619
[SIGHS] That I don't know.

09:45.620 --> 09:48.239
But look, with Halliday gone,

09:48.240 --> 09:50.399
he's gotta be looking for another fence.

09:50.400 --> 09:51.967
Maybe he's already found one.

09:51.968 --> 09:54.959
- I doubt it.
- What if he does?

09:54.960 --> 09:58.099
There's so much heat. Whoever buys them,

09:58.100 --> 09:59.899
they're gonna keep them under wraps,

09:59.900 --> 10:03.000
maybe for years and years. Fuck. [SIGHS]

10:05.188 --> 10:07.232
You shouldn't have killed Halliday.

10:09.650 --> 10:11.399
Well, I did, okay?

10:11.400 --> 10:14.039
- What's done is done.
- We've fucking blown it.

10:14.040 --> 10:15.739
I'm never gonna get to read them.

10:15.740 --> 10:18.159
When did you become such a goddamn baby?

10:18.160 --> 10:21.359
I told you, this is more
than about money to me.

10:21.360 --> 10:23.619
It's more than about
money to me, too, okay?

10:23.620 --> 10:25.459
I told you I loved the man,

10:25.460 --> 10:28.179
and it meant something that he loved me.

10:28.180 --> 10:30.579
I mean, there were versions
of me in some of his books.

10:30.580 --> 10:32.089
Not whole characters,

10:32.090 --> 10:34.399
but snippets.

10:34.400 --> 10:35.969
I know it.

10:37.220 --> 10:40.619
- I never read any versions of you.
- I said snippets.

10:40.620 --> 10:42.049
I'm just as desperate as you are

10:42.050 --> 10:43.840
to get ahold of those manuscripts.

10:43.852 --> 10:46.605
To see if you're in there?

10:48.060 --> 10:49.772
We gotta grab the kid's parents.

10:49.773 --> 10:51.799
- What?
- For collateral, Morris,

10:51.800 --> 10:53.319
to trade the books for.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.649
[SCOFFS] Kidnapping is not my thing.

10:55.650 --> 10:57.419
Oh, well, we'd better
make it our fucking thing,

10:57.420 --> 10:59.117
'cause we've killed people, Morris.

10:59.118 --> 11:01.320
It's all coming to a head.

11:03.200 --> 11:05.839
Have you gone mad?

11:05.840 --> 11:07.999
She's not gonna present a danger.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.089
How can you know that if
she got Brady in her head?

11:10.090 --> 11:11.659
Yeah, well, lots of
people hear voices, okay?

11:11.660 --> 11:13.519
As much as 20% of the population,

11:13.520 --> 11:16.130
and that doesn't necessarily
mean mental illness.

11:16.134 --> 11:18.178
For the ones who heard Brady, it did.

11:19.040 --> 11:20.429
I know you want to help, but...

11:20.430 --> 11:21.440
[DOOR OPENS]

11:22.130 --> 11:24.260
Hey.

11:24.270 --> 11:26.329
Hey, Lou.

11:26.330 --> 11:30.060
- Welcome back.
- Thank you.

11:32.600 --> 11:36.099
Okay, uh, I got... I'm
sorry, I gotta say, um,

11:36.100 --> 11:41.200
I really cannot even
convey my gratitude.

11:41.201 --> 11:44.286
I can't even begin.

11:44.287 --> 11:45.859
Never would have been able to hold up

11:45.860 --> 11:49.279
without the support.

11:49.280 --> 11:51.699
And the people in this room...

11:51.700 --> 11:55.139
you were all I had...

11:55.140 --> 11:57.210
and I will never forget it.

11:59.590 --> 12:02.679
Lou, I worry about you being unstable.

12:02.680 --> 12:05.439
I'm concerned for you,
and I'm concerned for Holly,

12:05.440 --> 12:07.394
should you be living with her.

12:08.860 --> 12:10.679
Yeah, I totally get that.

12:10.680 --> 12:15.639
I... I totally get that, and
I get that I need counseling.

12:15.640 --> 12:17.879
I... [CHUCKLES RUEFULLY]

12:17.880 --> 12:23.179
I can't take this all on alone.

12:23.180 --> 12:24.859
But... [SIGHS]

12:24.860 --> 12:28.819
the idea that I would pose
a threat to any of you...

12:28.820 --> 12:31.819
You're the closest thing
I have to family.

12:31.820 --> 12:34.399
Which is what you said to
Brady before shooting him

12:34.400 --> 12:35.463
in the eye socket.

12:37.424 --> 12:40.509
You're right to worry.

12:40.510 --> 12:42.721
He is. I worry.

12:44.600 --> 12:48.199
And I'm gonna move on...

12:48.200 --> 12:52.605
and I know that that starts
with moving on from Brady.

12:55.000 --> 12:59.060
[SILVERWARE CLATTERING]

13:00.200 --> 13:02.200
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.

13:03.760 --> 13:06.609
My desperation put this all in motion.

13:06.610 --> 13:10.480
My inability to provide
for this family...

13:12.220 --> 13:14.259
Peter wouldn't be mixed up in
any of this if I had just...

13:14.260 --> 13:15.599
First of all, we have no idea

13:15.600 --> 13:16.999
exactly what Peter is mixed up in.

13:17.000 --> 13:19.879
Peter is sending us the money, Marjorie.

13:19.880 --> 13:23.739
Can't you see that?

13:23.740 --> 13:25.739
[SILVERWARE CLATTERS]

13:25.740 --> 13:29.199
God sends manna from heaven,
but cash tends to drop

13:29.200 --> 13:30.959
from more ordinary sources.

13:30.960 --> 13:36.499
Bank loans, inheritances.

13:36.500 --> 13:38.609
You got a rich uncle
we don't know about?

13:38.610 --> 13:41.459
He's sending us the money, Marjorie.

13:41.460 --> 13:44.282
He's doing whatever he can
to help out because I can't.

13:46.576 --> 13:48.819
Wait, an interview on television?

13:48.820 --> 13:51.619
CNT-Ohio is offering her $15,000

13:51.620 --> 13:53.165
for a live-camera sit-down.

13:53.166 --> 13:56.499
And you think that's a good idea?

13:56.500 --> 13:58.399
[STAMMERS] It's a lucrative one.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.599
Lou has no money. I...
I'm gonna be a part of it

14:00.600 --> 14:02.179
to make sure the wheels don't come off.

14:02.180 --> 14:04.039
Yeah, but I think that
the best thing for her

14:04.040 --> 14:06.478
therapeutically would
be just be to kind of,

14:06.479 --> 14:07.969
you know, disappear.

14:07.970 --> 14:09.619
She killed Mr. Mercedes.

14:09.620 --> 14:12.019
She's not likely to find anonymity,

14:12.020 --> 14:13.659
and I'm not sure I would advise her to.

14:13.660 --> 14:16.481
I mean, it could be a career.
A book, a movie.

14:16.482 --> 14:19.199
Wait, a book?

14:19.200 --> 14:21.069
I don't know about that.

14:22.300 --> 14:23.460
Look, I'll call you back.

14:23.470 --> 14:25.079
I'm about to meet with a client.

14:25.080 --> 14:26.610
Okay, bye.

14:26.616 --> 14:29.399
Oh, okay, bye.

14:29.400 --> 14:30.869
[PHONE BEEPS]

14:30.870 --> 14:34.457
[BELL TOLLING]

14:41.548 --> 14:44.089
Peter?

14:44.090 --> 14:45.839
Mr. Finkelstein.

14:45.840 --> 14:48.399
Are you sure you weren't followed?

14:48.400 --> 14:50.879
I'm as sure as I can be, yeah.

14:50.880 --> 14:54.379
I take it that...

14:54.380 --> 14:56.353
Ms. Silver kind of filled you in?

14:56.354 --> 14:58.180
She did, yeah.

15:01.000 --> 15:02.439
Why here?

15:02.440 --> 15:03.879
[LAUGHS]

15:03.880 --> 15:06.739
Sorry, it's just, I figured
no one would come here.

15:06.740 --> 15:09.719
Plus, sanctuary laws, right?

15:09.720 --> 15:12.036
Where police can't enter.
Isn't that kind of a law?

15:12.037 --> 15:13.979
Oh, not really. [STAMMERS]

15:13.980 --> 15:15.799
The government is free
to go after the church,

15:15.800 --> 15:19.289
it just chooses not to. [SNIFFS]

15:19.290 --> 15:23.859
So, I'm your client, you're my lawyer,

15:23.860 --> 15:25.459
and this is privileged.

15:25.460 --> 15:28.679
Well, for your protection and mine, yes.

15:28.680 --> 15:30.930
- Shall I lay it out?
- Yeah.

15:32.580 --> 15:35.639
For starters, you are in
possession of stolen property.

15:35.640 --> 15:36.759
But I found it.

15:36.760 --> 15:39.029
Doesn't matter, the property was stolen

15:39.030 --> 15:40.979
over the course of a robbery

15:40.980 --> 15:43.139
during which at least
one man was murdered,

15:43.140 --> 15:45.249
thus making it a murder-robbery,

15:45.250 --> 15:47.969
- which isn't good.
- [DOOR OPENS]

15:47.970 --> 15:50.700
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:54.160 --> 15:56.620
But I didn't know anything
about the robbery.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.439
But you do now,

15:58.440 --> 16:01.039
and I take it that you've
known about it for some time.

16:01.040 --> 16:04.279
You're not going to like this, okay?

16:04.280 --> 16:08.239
But under Ohio law...

16:08.240 --> 16:10.359
anyone and everyone
involved in the robbery,

16:10.360 --> 16:13.899
including those who were
handling the stolen goods,

16:13.900 --> 16:15.599
is guilty of murder.

16:15.600 --> 16:16.680
What?

16:17.920 --> 16:20.230
As guilty as if he pulled
the trigger himself.

16:22.810 --> 16:24.439
How can that be?

16:24.440 --> 16:27.319
Because politicians get
to draft penal codes,

16:27.320 --> 16:30.448
none of whom want to be
viewed as being soft on crime.

16:30.449 --> 16:34.439
And home robberies, they
get prosecutorial overkill

16:34.440 --> 16:36.779
because that's what terrifies
everyone the most.

16:36.780 --> 16:38.979
I didn't invade anybody's home.

16:38.980 --> 16:41.199
Hey, hey, hey. [STAMMERS]

16:41.200 --> 16:45.159
My advice is for you to authorize me

16:45.160 --> 16:46.279
to go to the police.

16:46.280 --> 16:49.129
I can try and arrange a proffer,

16:49.130 --> 16:51.199
broker a deal, which I think I can get.

16:51.200 --> 16:53.339
I can't guarantee no time,

16:53.340 --> 16:56.959
but if you fully cooperate...

16:56.960 --> 16:58.639
Ida says you may have information

16:58.640 --> 17:01.460
on who killed Rothstein.

17:02.640 --> 17:05.939
I... I don't know his name,
but I can give a description.

17:05.940 --> 17:07.398
All right,

17:07.400 --> 17:09.598
and you would need to return
all of the money you found

17:09.599 --> 17:11.440
plus the books.

17:12.839 --> 17:15.608
I gave the most money to
my folks, and they spent it.

17:15.609 --> 17:17.499
Oh, that isn't good,

17:17.500 --> 17:21.165
but the returning of the
books is far more important.

17:22.359 --> 17:23.664
What about my parents?

17:23.665 --> 17:25.779
Would they get in trouble
for using the cash?

17:25.780 --> 17:27.638
It... it's possible but unlikely,

17:27.640 --> 17:30.172
since they had no reason
to know that it was stolen.

17:30.173 --> 17:33.479
Look, you have something
to offer: the manuscripts,

17:33.480 --> 17:35.859
plus information that
could lead to the arrest

17:35.860 --> 17:37.348
of Rothstein's killer.

17:39.940 --> 17:42.769
[SIGHS]

17:42.770 --> 17:45.559
See what you can get from the police,

17:45.560 --> 17:47.919
- then I'll decide.
- Wait, no, no, no.

17:47.920 --> 17:49.879
It's not gonna be that simple.

17:49.880 --> 17:52.019
Any deal they offer

17:52.020 --> 17:55.680
will be conditioned
upon meeting you first.

18:03.000 --> 18:04.039
[KNOCKS ON GLASS]

18:04.040 --> 18:07.579
Hey, got something for you.

18:07.580 --> 18:10.849
[GRUNTS]

18:10.850 --> 18:15.080
That's him right there, the Saubers kid.

18:17.160 --> 18:19.089
In the bookstore?

18:19.090 --> 18:21.601
They it in Halliday's desk
under a pile of shit.

18:21.602 --> 18:22.989
I thought all the security footage

18:22.990 --> 18:24.679
and the computers were gone?

18:24.680 --> 18:26.859
Yeah, well, they were,
but for some reason,

18:26.860 --> 18:29.064
Halliday had a photocopy
of that in his desk.

18:29.065 --> 18:30.419
And you got this how?

18:30.420 --> 18:32.519
Uh, Montez sent it over.

18:32.520 --> 18:35.865
Probably trying to scratch
your balls a little bit.

18:35.866 --> 18:39.859
- Nasty image.
- [LAUGHS] Look,

18:39.860 --> 18:41.699
we know that he maybe found the books,

18:41.700 --> 18:43.759
we know that he was in
there, and we also know

18:43.760 --> 18:45.899
that we have a dead rare
book collector on our hands.

18:45.900 --> 18:47.099
And you said it yourself:

18:47.100 --> 18:48.920
you don't believe in coincidences.

18:53.040 --> 18:54.259
Our window is closing.

18:54.260 --> 18:55.801
We need to grab the mother

18:55.802 --> 18:57.579
and make clear to the
gimp that we have her

18:57.580 --> 18:58.999
and that if he wants to see her,

18:59.000 --> 19:00.579
he keeps his mouth shut.

19:00.580 --> 19:02.999
We can use Marjorie's
phone to text Petey-boy

19:03.000 --> 19:06.104
that he's got a problem and
better produce those books.

19:06.105 --> 19:08.059
[BOTTLES CLATTER]

19:08.060 --> 19:09.809
So where do we grab her?

19:09.810 --> 19:11.699
Anywhere is risky... [SIGHS]

19:11.700 --> 19:13.945
but probably less risky at the house.

19:13.946 --> 19:16.919
The father has a PTSD
support group meeting

19:16.920 --> 19:18.219
tonight at 7:30.

19:18.220 --> 19:19.229
Let's go then.

19:19.230 --> 19:21.059
[CLEARS THROAT, CLICKS TONGUE]

19:21.060 --> 19:24.371
We can't wait, Morris, if we're serious.

19:24.372 --> 19:25.998
[SIGHS]

19:31.504 --> 19:34.882
You really think you were in the novels?

19:36.280 --> 19:39.510
In various tiny incarnations, yes.

19:40.420 --> 19:42.179
We really loved each other.

19:42.180 --> 19:45.739
I was maybe the only woman
who could return more shit

19:45.740 --> 19:48.399
than Rothstein could dish out.

19:48.400 --> 19:50.439
He was putty in my hands.

19:50.440 --> 19:51.941
I think it scared him.

19:53.500 --> 19:55.699
Who were you?

19:55.700 --> 19:56.859
In the books.

19:56.860 --> 20:00.939
Oh... oh, many different people.

20:00.940 --> 20:03.039
[SNIFFS] But mainly...

20:03.040 --> 20:05.179
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:05.180 --> 20:06.620
I was Susan.

20:08.100 --> 20:10.160
Susan Harris?

20:11.500 --> 20:12.859
No fucking way.

20:12.860 --> 20:15.279
Read the description
of her in "The Runner."

20:15.280 --> 20:16.759
That's me.

20:16.760 --> 20:18.579
Also the way she spoke.

20:18.580 --> 20:20.136
That was me.

20:21.880 --> 20:23.339
You were Susan?

20:23.340 --> 20:25.760
Jimmy's first love.

20:26.880 --> 20:29.019
And mine. [LAUGHS]

20:29.020 --> 20:34.179
Many nights, she would be...

20:34.180 --> 20:36.109
the last person I thought of.

20:36.110 --> 20:38.689
[LAUGHS] I used to joke

20:38.690 --> 20:40.419
I had carpal Harris syndrome.

20:40.420 --> 20:43.880
[LAUGHING]

20:45.420 --> 20:47.279
That was you?

20:47.280 --> 20:50.699
The way he would write about her...

20:50.700 --> 20:53.759
don't tell me he didn't love me.

20:53.760 --> 20:56.419
That's who Jimmy ended
up with in the end,

20:56.420 --> 20:58.279
if it was the end.

20:58.280 --> 21:02.539
I was in love with Susan
when I was, like, 16.

21:02.540 --> 21:05.179
I bet you never thought
you could have her for real,

21:05.180 --> 21:06.679
did you?

21:06.680 --> 21:09.439
<i>[SENSUAL ROCK MUSIC]</i>

21:09.440 --> 21:10.639
No.

21:10.640 --> 21:13.399
- [LAUGHS]
- Fuck.

21:13.400 --> 21:15.199
- Yes, see?
- [GROANING]

21:15.200 --> 21:17.899
Jimmy, Jimmy, this is Susan.

21:17.900 --> 21:18.979
Susan.

21:18.980 --> 21:21.197
You know what I used
to call you? My love.

21:21.198 --> 21:23.779
My love. Jimmy, my love, my love!

21:23.780 --> 21:26.117
Jimmy Gold! Pure!

21:26.118 --> 21:27.577
Gold! [GROANS]

21:27.578 --> 21:29.479
[DOOR OPENS]

21:29.480 --> 21:31.207
Hey.

21:31.220 --> 21:32.579
Hey.

21:32.580 --> 21:33.869
How do I look?

21:33.870 --> 21:35.709
You look great.

21:35.710 --> 21:37.829
Thanks. Lou ready?

21:37.830 --> 21:38.899
Uh, she's upstairs.

21:38.900 --> 21:41.466
- I'll let her know you're here.
- Okay, thanks.

21:41.467 --> 21:43.549
You got a second?

21:43.550 --> 21:45.555
Yeah, sure.

21:51.760 --> 21:54.269
Your relationship with
Montez, it's good?

21:54.270 --> 21:55.849
Why?

21:55.850 --> 21:57.139
I met with the Saubers kid.

21:57.140 --> 21:59.025
Obviously, he's in a bit of trouble.

21:59.026 --> 22:02.479
Wants to get with the DA
to try to set up a proffer,

22:02.480 --> 22:03.959
which figures to be a difficult sell,

22:03.960 --> 22:08.039
so I was wondering if you
could make a positive call

22:08.040 --> 22:09.739
on his behalf in advance?

22:09.740 --> 22:12.859
Well, I... I haven't
actually met the kid.

22:12.860 --> 22:15.251
Met his dad. Does he
have the manuscripts?

22:15.252 --> 22:18.336
I can't reveal privileged information.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.714
You could deny he's got them.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.129
He's got them.

22:23.130 --> 22:24.679
I can't say anything

22:24.680 --> 22:27.419
other than it is a dangerous situation,

22:27.420 --> 22:30.098
like you have said, so
the sooner that we get...

22:30.099 --> 22:31.539
I'll call Montez.

22:31.540 --> 22:33.539
Thanks. It could be a big help.

22:33.540 --> 22:37.272
Well, I'm off to hair and makeup.

22:37.273 --> 22:39.191
Okay.

22:42.980 --> 22:44.179
All right, I'll see you later.

22:44.180 --> 22:45.579
- Wish me luck.
- Break a leg.

22:45.580 --> 22:47.270
Thanks.

22:48.580 --> 22:50.449
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

22:50.450 --> 22:52.939
So, what was that about?

22:52.940 --> 22:55.999
Ah, just stuff. [CLEARS THROAT]

22:56.000 --> 22:57.579
What do you mean, "just stuff"?

22:57.580 --> 22:58.959
I mean,

22:58.960 --> 23:00.419
I'm a full partner here,

23:00.420 --> 23:03.173
and add to that, I was eavesdropping.

23:03.174 --> 23:06.092
Is Roland gonna represent
the Saubers boy?

23:06.093 --> 23:07.970
He could be.

23:08.980 --> 23:10.514
The one with the manuscripts.

23:10.515 --> 23:12.999
It's a good thing, Holly.

23:13.000 --> 23:14.659
Get the books back, get the reward.

23:14.660 --> 23:16.319
Yeah, but it's also a dangerous thing,

23:16.320 --> 23:17.771
a very risky thing.

23:17.772 --> 23:21.108
And you attacked a serial
killer with a paperweight.

23:23.760 --> 23:24.939
[DOOR OPENS]

23:24.940 --> 23:28.399
Is he optimistic, Finkelstein?

23:28.400 --> 23:30.159
I don't know.

23:30.160 --> 23:32.659
The kid's stepped in some serious shit.

23:32.660 --> 23:34.779
His best bet is probably to talk to me.

23:34.780 --> 23:36.219
I still don't know where he is,

23:36.220 --> 23:37.704
if that's where you're headed.

23:37.705 --> 23:40.619
Yeah, well, the next time
he knocks on your door...

23:40.620 --> 23:41.859
- Oh... [STAMMERS]
- We'd better find him

23:41.860 --> 23:43.560
before the killer does.

23:44.410 --> 23:45.959
<i>- ... attorney, Roland Finkelstein.</i>
- There she is.

23:45.960 --> 23:48.669
<i>I cannot even imagine what it was like</i>

23:48.670 --> 23:51.719
<i>for you to hear that verdict... </i>

23:51.720 --> 23:52.999
<i>and then the sentencing.</i>

23:53.000 --> 23:56.779
<i>Yeah, it was kind of crazy.</i>

23:56.780 --> 23:59.840
- Yeah.
- <i>So you feel justice was done?</i>

24:03.540 --> 24:06.149
<i>Well, I'm not complaining.</i>

24:06.150 --> 24:07.379
<i>The district attorney is.</i>

24:07.380 --> 24:11.059
<i>She and many others say
that this was wrong,</i>

24:11.060 --> 24:14.609
<i>that you were basically
deemed to be above the law.</i>

24:14.610 --> 24:18.639
<i>Well... that whole... </i>

24:18.640 --> 24:20.569
<i>"nobody's above the law" thing, I mean,</i>

24:20.570 --> 24:24.679
<i>that's kind of a myth, really.</i>

24:24.680 --> 24:26.256
Jeez.

24:26.257 --> 24:27.923
<i>- "A myth"?
- Yeah, well,</i>

24:27.924 --> 24:30.539
<i>it's only the little people
that can't be above the law.</i>

24:30.540 --> 24:32.019
<i>The big people... </i>

24:32.020 --> 24:34.719
<i>Nixon, he got pardoned.</i>

24:34.720 --> 24:36.359
<i>He was above the law.</i>

24:36.360 --> 24:40.299
<i>The banks that were "too big to fail."</i>

24:40.300 --> 24:43.849
<i>People in Ohio died because of them.</i>

24:43.850 --> 24:46.039
<i>They didn't go to jail.</i>

24:46.040 --> 24:49.349
<i>The banks didn't literally kill anyone.</i>

24:49.350 --> 24:52.179
<i>O.J. did, Teddy Kennedy did,</i>

24:52.180 --> 24:54.559
<i>George Zimmerman did... the guy that... </i>

24:54.560 --> 24:55.599
Pretty... pretty good.

24:55.600 --> 24:56.959
I mean, really good, actually.

24:56.960 --> 24:59.799
But she... she does seem...

24:59.800 --> 25:01.099
- Crazy.
- Yeah.

25:01.100 --> 25:04.689
<i>This idea that nobody is above the law,</i>

25:04.690 --> 25:06.319
<i>not even the president
of the United States... </i>

25:06.320 --> 25:09.249
<i>I mean, Monica, it's a joke.</i>

25:09.250 --> 25:12.719
<i>Clinton, Nixon, Andrew Jackson,</i>

25:12.720 --> 25:15.719
<i>they all broke laws.</i>

25:15.720 --> 25:19.499
<i>Even Bush... I mean,
if you count starting a war</i>

25:19.500 --> 25:20.559
<i>under false pretenses</i>

25:20.560 --> 25:23.809
<i>so that your vice president
can get a gazillion dollars</i>

25:23.810 --> 25:26.619
<i>in... in private defense contracts.</i>

25:26.620 --> 25:28.679
<i>- [LAUGHS]
- People are still dying... </i>

25:28.680 --> 25:30.862
She needs to sit down and shut up.

25:30.863 --> 25:33.139
This kind of talk is
very dangerous for her.

25:33.140 --> 25:35.149
- That rhetoric?
- <i>Are you worried</i>

25:35.150 --> 25:38.719
<i>that what you did might
spur on other vigilantes?</i>

25:38.720 --> 25:40.179
<i>- Well...
- I mean,</i>

25:40.180 --> 25:43.179
<i>let's take this bookstore
owner, for example.</i>

25:43.180 --> 25:46.519
<i>You no sooner were set free
than someone else decides</i>

25:46.520 --> 25:48.079
<i>to take the law into their own hands</i>

25:48.080 --> 25:49.739
and avenge a sex offender.

25:49.740 --> 25:53.039
- I fail to see any connection.
- Well, it's eye-for-an-eye justice.

25:53.040 --> 25:54.799
Isn't that exactly

25:54.800 --> 25:56.972
what the district
attorney warned against?

25:56.973 --> 26:00.179
I was just speaking for myself.

26:00.180 --> 26:03.559
I wasn't speaking for society at large.

26:03.560 --> 26:07.940
But if I was to speak
for society at large...

26:07.950 --> 26:10.109
When the law doesn't work,

26:10.110 --> 26:13.209
<i>when government officials
are allowed to commit crimes,</i>

26:13.210 --> 26:15.599
when the people that we
trust to uphold the law

26:15.600 --> 26:17.139
are the same ones that are breaking it,

26:17.140 --> 26:19.409
there needs to be a revolution.

26:19.410 --> 26:21.199
Brother.

