42:20.900 --> 42:22.279
is all about control, okay?

42:22.280 --> 42:23.832
I need to be in control.

42:23.833 --> 42:25.819
Nobody's in control of their life.

42:25.820 --> 42:27.099
Do you think I'm in control of mine?

42:27.100 --> 42:29.359
I'm different than you and other
people, and you know it, okay?

42:29.360 --> 42:31.419
I need to have everything
in a certain place.

42:31.420 --> 42:33.299
Everything has to be in a
certain order, all right?

42:33.300 --> 42:38.009
I need patterns and routines and...

42:38.010 --> 42:39.799
And?

42:39.800 --> 42:43.699
And...

42:43.700 --> 42:46.699
when I heard that Roland was
representing the Saubers boy,

42:46.700 --> 42:49.799
I became so afraid, okay?

42:49.800 --> 42:52.959
Because it's dangerous.

42:52.960 --> 42:56.119
I got scared, and also
it made me realize...

42:56.120 --> 42:59.280
and that's why.

43:00.460 --> 43:03.789
You're gonna have to
connect a few more dots.

43:03.790 --> 43:07.379
[SIGHS]

43:07.380 --> 43:12.139
If I continue to see him,
I might fall in love with him...

43:12.140 --> 43:14.539
and I'll lose control.

43:14.540 --> 43:17.169
You know, I loved Oli...

43:17.170 --> 43:20.799
and when you love people,
you grow branches or limbs,

43:20.800 --> 43:23.939
and they are outside
of your jurisdiction,

43:23.940 --> 43:25.579
and I'm... [STAMMERS, SIGHS]

43:25.580 --> 43:27.603
It's too emotionally unwieldy for me

43:27.604 --> 43:29.230
to end up with someone else in the end.

43:32.060 --> 43:35.219
That's the dumbest
thing I've ever heard.

43:35.220 --> 43:37.479
You can't break up with someone

43:37.480 --> 43:39.899
'cause you're afraid
you might love them.

43:39.900 --> 43:43.919
[SIGHS] It's... it's been a long process

43:43.920 --> 43:45.879
getting to this point.

43:45.880 --> 43:48.359
You know, being able to
function in the outside world.

43:48.360 --> 43:50.079
I have to protect myself

43:50.080 --> 43:53.479
however I can, you know? I need...

43:53.480 --> 43:55.959
I need to be in control.

43:55.960 --> 44:00.339
Well, I'm no expert on
the outside world stuff,

44:00.340 --> 44:05.639
but... it seems to me...

44:05.640 --> 44:09.039
one of the main perks is
getting to love people,

44:09.040 --> 44:10.640
being loved back.

44:13.160 --> 44:15.899
Not everyone gets to have that.

44:15.900 --> 44:17.359
Why can't you?

44:17.360 --> 44:20.199
Leap and the net will appear.

44:20.200 --> 44:21.799
- Isn't that what Jerome told you?
- [SIGHS]

44:21.800 --> 44:23.536
It's good advice.

44:24.800 --> 44:28.220
If you like this man, go be with him.

44:29.260 --> 44:32.329
Dumping him out of
fear of losing control

44:32.330 --> 44:34.289
just makes you a dope.

44:34.290 --> 44:36.879
[SIGHS]

44:36.880 --> 44:38.840
You're not a dope.

44:40.800 --> 44:45.839
- [PHONE RINGING]
- <i>[TENSE ROCK MUSIC]</i>

44:45.840 --> 44:48.889
Marjorie, Marjorie, come on.

44:48.890 --> 44:52.539
<i>I'm gonna make this short
because time is not my friend,</i>

44:52.540 --> 44:56.349
<i>it's not yours,
and it's definitely not... </i>

44:56.350 --> 44:57.946
<i>- hers.
- [MUFFLED SCREAMING]</i>

44:57.947 --> 44:59.449
Oh, Jesus!

44:59.450 --> 45:01.149
You call the police,

45:01.150 --> 45:02.459
we kill her.

45:02.460 --> 45:04.449
Simple as fucking that.

45:04.450 --> 45:06.039
<i>Do we want to kill her?</i>

45:06.040 --> 45:08.369
<i>No, no, we don't. It's messy.</i>

45:08.370 --> 45:11.539
What I want is the John
Rothstein books...

45:11.540 --> 45:13.085
I don't have the fucking books!

45:13.086 --> 45:17.839
Which your little prick
fuck of a son has.

45:17.840 --> 45:20.699
You make contact with
the little pricky-dicky-do,

45:20.700 --> 45:23.629
and you tell him to deal with us.

45:23.630 --> 45:25.764
<i>You need to give your
